name: FGameplayEffectCustomExecutionOutput
doc: Struct representing the output of a custom gameplay effect execution.

methods.name: AddOutputModifier
methods.doc: Add the specified evaluated data to the execution's output modifiers

methods.name: AreGameplayCuesHandledManually
methods.doc: Accessor for determining if GameplayCue events have already been handled

methods.name: GetOutputModifiers
methods.doc: Simple accessor to output modifiers of the execution

methods.name: GetOutputModifiersRef
methods.doc: Returns direct access to output modifiers of the execution (avoid copy)

methods.name: IsStackCountHandledManually
methods.doc: Simple accessor for determining whether the execution has manually handled the stack count or not

methods.name: MarkConditionalGameplayEffectsToTrigger
methods.doc: Mark that the execution wants conditional gameplay effects to trigger

methods.name: MarkGameplayCuesHandledManually
methods.doc: Mark that the execution wants conditional gameplay effects to trigger

methods.name: MarkStackCountHandledManually
methods.doc: Mark that the execution has manually handled the stack count and the GE system should not attempt to automatically act upon it for emitted modifiers

methods.name: ShouldTriggerConditionalGameplayEffects
methods.doc: Simple accessor for determining whether the execution wants conditional gameplay effects to trigger or not
